title: Cicada
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: In the form of a cicada, with bulging eyes on head, large veined wings, and ribbed body. Reverse features underside of insect, textured belly likely intended as striker. Head serves as lid, hinged on reverse or underside so that it flips back when opened.
